<HEADLINE> 15 People Injured in Train Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A head-on collision of two trains on
a narrow-gauge railway near the Nova Vcelnice station, the
Jindrichuv Hradec district, injured at least 15 people Saturday,
three of them seriously.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 12:45 p.m., when a train from
Nova Vcelnice collided shortly after the start with another train
going in the opposite direction, the local media reported.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers rushed to the spot and some of the injured was sent to
a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
