<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz, also first deputy prime minister and commander of the
National Guard, arrived in Kuwait on Saturday on a three-day state
visit.
</P>
<P>
The visit comes in the context of consultations between the two
countries and is aimed to boost bilateral ties, said Kuwaiti First
Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Sabah al-Ahmad al-Jaber
al-Sabah in a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti and Saudi newspapers reported that the two officials
will hold talks on promoting bilateral cooperation and on affairs
of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), the Gulf Arab alliance which
also groups the United Arab Emirates, Oman, Qatar and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also discuss the issues of the Kuwaiti
hostages held by Iraq since its 1990 invasion of Kuwait, the
Palestinian course, and the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
