<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stops Iraqi Cargo Ship in Territorial Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait on Saturday stopped an
Iraqi cargo ship in its territorial waters for violating the
international economic embargo imposed on Iraq since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti Interior Ministry announced in a statement that the
Kuwaiti coast guard stopped the Iraqi ship coming from the Iraqi Um
Qasr Port on its way to the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
The ship, carrying 231 tons of urea fertilizers, 31 tons of
liquorice, 37 tons of leather with a captain and 16 seamen on
board, was the fourth stopped by Kuwait in the past one month in
its territorial waters for violating the ban on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti coast guard stopped on June 24 an Iraqi ship
carrying 449 heads of sheep and another Iraqi oil tanker carrying
650 tons of fuel gas on their way to the UAE. On June 12, they
intercepted an Iraqi ship carrying leather, wool and legume. They
stopped in May an Iraqi ship carrying date and grains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
