<HEADLINE> Palestinians to Declare Independent State This Year Despite Foreign Pressure: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Palestinian National
Council Selim Zanoun said Saturday the independent Palestinian
state will be declared this year according to the international
resolutions in spite of foreign pressure.
</P>
<P>
Zanoun told reporters at the council headquarters on the eve of
the inauguration of the Palestinian Central Council meetings in
Gaza on Sunday on the issue of the Palestinian independence.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian state will be verified shortly, and the
international community will support the cause, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said that there still exists international
pressure to delay the declaration of the state.
</P>
<P>
Refuting the Israeli threats to retaliate if the Palestinian
state is declared unilaterally, Zanoun said the Oslo Agreement does
not require consultation with Israel over this topic, but the
Palestinian people are always eager to verify the state with
Israel's approval.
</P>
<P>
However, if Israel insists on its procrastination, The
Palestinians have to embody the state, he noted, adding,"We will
seek international legitimacy for preserving our security and
protecting us from any Israeli aggressions."
</P>
<P>
Referring to the U.S. stance on the declaration of the
Palestinian state, Zanoun expressed hope that the U.S.
administration would recognize the Palestinian state as this
recognition.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government has not yet officially notified the
Palestinian side of its position on the unilateral declaration of
the Palestinian independent state, he said.
</P>
<P>
The United States said last year that the declaration of the
Palestinian state should be made with Israel's approval.
</P>
<P>
As to the agenda of the Central Council meetings, Zanoun said
the attendees would mull over the practical preparations for
declaring the state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
