<HEADLINE> Arafat Calls on EU to Help Relaunch Mideast Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian President Yasser Arafat
Saturday called on European Union (EU) to play an effective and
big role in helping relaunch the Middle East peace process, which
he said is at a dangerous and difficult turning point.
</P>
<P>
Arafat made the appeal after a meeting with French President
Jacques Chirac at the Elysee presidential palace here.
</P>
<P>
According to French presidential spokeswoman Catherine Colonna,
Arafat expressed his concern about the perspective of the peace
process during his meeting with Chirac, whose country took over
the rotating presidency of EU on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian president listed a series of barriers in the
peace process, including Israel's delay in implementing its
agreement with Palestinians over withdrawal of troops from West
Bank, and the continuation of illegal construction of Jewish
settlement on Arab land.
</P>
<P>
Chirac reaffirmed the commitment of EU to the principles which
serve as the basis for the peace process, including the United
Nations Security Council Resolution 242 which calls for the
pullout of Israeli troops from all Arab territories it occupied in
1967, according to Colonna.
</P>
<P>
Israel has delayed the carrying out of a third phase of pullout
from the West Bank scheduled for June 23 and Israeli leaders have
hardened their position recently over Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Israel has also threatened to crack down any demonstration by
Palestinians after June 23 and to foil the Palestinian plan to
declare independence in September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
