<HEADLINE> New Container Berths Built in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The second-phase construction of
Yantian Port in south China's Shenzhen City, which borders Hong
Kong, was approved today by a state expert team.
</P>
<P>
The facility, taking three years to build and costing 4.7
billion Hong Kong dollars, consists of three container berths with
an annual handling capacity of 1.2 million TEUs.
</P>
<P>
It will increase the port's annual handling capacity to two
million TEUs.
</P>
<P>
Yantian Port has opened shipping routes to the United States,
Europe, Oceania and many Asian countries. About 30 international
shipping companies have established subsidiaries here.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen is one of China's special economic zones.  
</P>
</TEXT>
