<HEADLINE> Concert Held to Celebrate 3rd Anniversary of HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Artists of the Chinese mainland
and Hong Kong held a concert at the Hong Kong Coliseum Saturday
evening to mark the third anniversary of the establishment of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The prestigious Central Opera Theater Symphony Orchestra of
China, under the baton of Yan Liangkun, played the Spring Festival
Overture and the Dance of the Yao Tribe, bringing a festive
atmosphere to the audience.
</P>
<P>
Other programs include the Ode to Joy from Beethoven's Symphony
No.9 in D minor sung by the China National Symphony Orchestra
Chorus, the traditional Chinese music Beautiful Clouds Chasing the
Moon played by the Hong Kong Orchestra and the 1997 Home Coming
sung by the Hong Kong Children's Choir.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 people attended the concert, including Hong Kong
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and Director of the Liaison Office
of the Central People's Government in the HKSAR Jiang Enzhu.
</P>
