<HEADLINE> Six More Bodies from Boat Tragedy Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Six more bodies from the boat
tragedy which occurred on the Yangtze River on June 22 were
recovered today, bringing the death toll of the accident to 127.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here today, three people are
still missing and search and the rescue operation is continuing.
</P>
<P>
The passenger vessel Rong Jian, which was designed to carry a
maximum of 101 people, had 221 passengers on board when it hit a
rock and sank while sailing in foggy conditions on June 22.
</P>
<P>
The ship's owner and captain have been arrested and charged
with dereliction of duty. 
