<HEADLINE> China Gives Degrees to Dot-com Majors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China's first graduating class of
students majoring in electronic media have received their bachelor
's degrees from Central China Science and Technology University.
</P>
<P>
All 22 graduating seniors from the Web News Media class have
been hired by dot-com companies.
</P>
<P>
Students in the school's electronic media program are required
to take courses in history and literature, mass media, multimedia
technology, computer language and database technology.
</P>
<P>
China's soaring development in Internet technology and fast
growing number of dot-com companies have inspired universities to
open majors in the media specialty.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University and Qinghua University will soon offer
classes in web news media.  
</P>
