<HEADLINE> Sight First Program Benefiting Tibetans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A medical team funded by the Sight
First China Action program performed cataract surgeries today in
China's Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
This is the third medical team sent to Tibet by the program in
the past two years. The first two teams helped restore eyesight to
about 1,500 cataract patients.
</P>
<P>
The Sight First China Action program was launched in 1997 by
the Ministry of Health, the Chinese Disabled Persons Federation,
and Lions Club International.
</P>
<P>
It aims to help 1.75 million Chinese people regain their
eyesight and train 11,000 ophthalmologists at rural hospitals
across the country between 1997 and 2001.
</P>
<P>
So far more than 1.2 million Chinese cataract patients have
received operations and some 11,000 medical workers have been
trained.  
</P>
</TEXT>
