<HEADLINE> Tour Organizers Say Three Riders Fail Blood Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Tour de France organizers said on
Saturday that three riders failed blood tests for hematocrite and
are now ineligible for the race.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said in Futuroscope, France that Russian rider
Serguei Ivanov, Italian Rossano Brasi and Slovenian Andrej
Hauptman were found with a hematocrite level in the blood above
the legal limit of 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the International Cycling Union (UCI) rules,
riders with a hematocrite level above 50 percent shall be stopped
from competition for two weeks.  
</P>
