<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Railway System Ready for Peak Travel Period </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The railway system in Shanghai,
China's largest economic and financial center, is prepared for
this summer's peak travel season, which starts today and ends
August 31.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Railway Bureau estimated that the city's rails
will carry 26 million passengers during the period, 1.7 million
more than the same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has formed a group to be responsible for safe and
punctual delivery of passengers.
</P>
<P>
Between July 1 and August 31, six temporary trains from
Shanghai to Dalian, Nanjing and Fuzhou will be added to the
schedule. And additional trains from Shanghai to Beijing and Jinan
will also be put on the list when needed.
</P>
<P>
Summer is the fourth travel peak period in China following the
Spring Festival in February, the Tomb-Sweeping Festival in April
and the May Day holiday.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of students are traveling to and from
eastern China during summer vacation, as colleges and universities
in the area have admitted more students from other parts of the
country in the past two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
