<HEADLINE> Egypt to Launch Second Telecom Satellite in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Egypt's second telecommunications
satellite, Nilesat 102, has been manufactured by a French
corporation and is scheduled to be launched on August 17, the head
of the Egyptian Satellites Company has said.
</P>
<P>
A letter from the Mattra Marconi company has said the satellite
has been fully tested and would be shipped from France to the Korou
space center in French Guyana, South America, for the launching,
the semi-official Akhbar El Yom newspaper on Saturday quoted Amin
Bassyouny as saying.
</P>
<P>
Egypt launched its first telecom satellite, Nilesat 101, in
April 1998, becoming the first country in the Arab world and Africa
to have its own satellite.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Information Minister Safwat el-Sharif has described the
upcoming launching of the country's second satellite as a new
turning point in the history of Egyptian media, and also a great
achievement reflecting Egypt's solid and confident access into the
satellite industry.
</P>
<P>
The new satellite will operate in accordance with the latest
digital technology, el-Sharif said last Wednesday, adding that it
will help provide new media services including distance education,
stock exchange activities, news transmission and Internet shopping.
</P>
</TEXT>
