<HEADLINE> Urgent: Nine Russian Soldiers Killed in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Nine Russian soldiers were killed
and seven others wounded in an explosion of mine landed by rebels
near Chechnya's village of Avtury, Russian presidential aide on
Chechnya Sergey Yastrzhembsky told reporters Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A federal motorized convoy that had been involved in the
fighting near south Chechnya's village of Serzhen-Yurt was heading
for the base of stationing when a protection armored vehicle hit a
land-mine near the village of Avtury close to Serzhen-Yurt, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Five people were killed on the spot and four others badly
wounded and later died. Another seven soldiers sustained wounds of
varying degrees, Yastrzhembsky said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yastrzhembsky denied reports by some media that
about 40 federal soldiers were killed in the continuous battle
near Serzhen-Yurt.
</P>
<P>
"The federal force has lost only 13 people with 18 wounded over
the five-day fighting near Serzhen-Yurt, killing over 100 of all
the 200-250 rebels and injuring scores of the others," he said.
</P>
<P>
A mop-up operation is still underway there, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
