<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Reiterates "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen
Saturday reiterated the country's "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Meeting here with Wang Guangying, vice president of the
National People's Congress of China, Hun Sen said the upholding of
the "one China" policy has been the consistent position of
Cambodia's King Norodom Sihanouk and that both parliament and the
government of the country will never change this position.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen pointed out that China's prosperity and powerfulness
will help maintain peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region
and the whole world.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the Chinese government's stand of
stabilizing its currency during the period of the Asian financial
crisis in 1997, saying that the act had helped speed up the
recovery of the Asian economy.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said that the Cambodia-China friendship has a long
history. "We will not only cherish the friendship established by
leaders of the older generation but also strengthen and further
develop this friendship," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said his government encourages Chinese companies to
invest in Cambodia, especially in the field of agriculture, and
welcomes Chinese tourists to come to his country.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Wang praised Cambodian government's
achievements in maintaining national sovereignty and developing
economy in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Wang and her party left here for Hong Kong Saturday morning at
the end of her five-day visit. 
</P>
