<P>
KFOR arrested the boy the same day, who admitted that he had
thrown a bomb at the stronghold, said a Yugoslav news agency
Tanjug report based on the press release. Following the explosion,
KFOR tightened security around all strongholds and intensified
inspection of vehicles and pedestrians. (Yugoslavia-Kosovo-KFOR)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma Friday criticized the
United States for refusing to send former Ukraine premier Palvo
Lazarenko back to Kiev for trial.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Friday, Lazarenko, detained in a federal prison in
San Francisco since February 1999, was convicted of money-
laundering by a Swiss court and given an 18-month suspended prison
term. Kuchma had repeatedly asked Washington to send back
Lazarenko, who is also on charges of misappropriating state
property, abuse of power and murder of a member of parliament. (
Ukraine-US-Lazarenko) 
</P>
</TEXT>
