<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Smuggling Defeats Bangladesh-Myanmar Border Trade Purpose </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Well-knit smugglers' chains along the
Bangladesh-Myanmar border have defeated the purpose of border
trade between the two countries, according to the Financial
Express on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The border trade between the two countries came into effect in
1995 with the major objective of containing informal trade between
Bangladesh and Myanmar. But syndicates of smugglers did otherwise,
marginalizing the volume of border trade.
</P>
<P>
The unofficial transaction is now greater than the official one.
Salt, cigarette, fish and narcotics are some of the major items
smuggled into Bangladesh and diesel, medicine and cement are items
going to the other side of the border.
</P>
<P>
Trawlers, cargo vessels and local small and large boats are
principal transports used in the movement of smuggling goods
between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
