<DOCNO> XIE20000701.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Foodgrain production Touches Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the ministry of agriculture, wheat production
recorded an all-time high of 74.25 million tons during 1999-2000,
up 3.47 million tons from the previous fiscal year. Rice
production was also higher at 88.25 million tons as against 86
million tons.
</P>
<P>
The record production was achieved despite the devastating
cyclone in Orissa and drought in Gujarat, Rajasthan and parts of
Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
The government has set a foodgrain production target of 210
million tons for 2000-2001 fiscal year. 
</P>
