</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazilian economy grew 3.1 percent during the
first quarter of this year, compared to the same period of 1999,
according to a Central Bank (BC) report published Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Bank said that this economic growth was possible because of
the strong recovery of the industrial sector, that grew 5.7
percent, compared to the same period of 1999. (Brazil-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Using a smart card and his dog's name as password,
U.S. President Bill Clinton Friday e-signed into law a bill that
gives electronic signatures the same status as their ink-and-paper
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The president inserted the smart card into a computer and typed
in his dog's name, Buddy, as the password. After a while, the
computer screen said: "The Electronic Signatures in Global and
National Commerce Act is now a law." The signing ceremony took
place in Congress Hall of Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
"It works," Clinton told the audience of about 100 local
college students.
</P>
<P>
He said Americans will soon be able to use the cards "for
everything from hiring a lawyer to closing a mortgage." (Clinton-
Bill)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia's economic indicators continued improving
despite a slight drop in non-oil and gas exports, according to the
Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS).
</P>
<P>
The monthly inflation rate jumped by 0.5 percent in June, down
from the 0.8-percent increase in May while the year-on-year
inflation in the month was 2.14 percent as compared with 2.86
percent in the same period last year. (Indonesia-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
