<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- The Foreign Ministers of the Organization of
Islamic Conference (OIC) Friday urged the industrial countries to
facilitate the transfer of technology to developing countries and
to lift all obstacles that impede this transfer particularly.
</P>
<P>
Islamic States have the inalienable right to acquire, use and
develop scientific and technological means to achieve their social,
economic and cultural development, they said in a Communique
issued at the end of their four-day 27th meeting here.  (OIC-
Technology)
</P>
