<DOCNO> XIE20000701.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greene Makes 100-200 Double </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Maurice Greene of the United States
won both the 100 meters and the 200 meters at the Golden Gala here
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Greene dashed home first over 100 meters with a time of 9.97
seconds, 0.18 seconds slower than his world record time of 9.79
set in Athens in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Greene, who won triple gold at the 1999 World Championships,
also won the meters event with ease finishing 0.27 seconds ahead
of second-placed Brazilian Claudinei Da Silva with a time of 20.02.
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad that I doubled up here because it gives me confidence.
The US trails are coming up and my goal is to win both the 100 and
the 200 meters at Sydney," said 25-year-old Greene.
</P>
<P>
In the field events, Norwegian Trine Hattestad set a new world
record in the women's javelin with a distance of 68.22 meters,
beating the previous record of 67.09 thrown by Greece's Mirela
Manjani Tzelili in Seville. 
</P>
