<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Indian Train Derailment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Two engine drivers of Howrah-
Amritsar Express were killed as the train rammed into the empty
rake of a passenger train between Ambala Cantt and the Ambala city
railway station in North India's Haryana state early Saturday
morning.
</P>
<P>
A local railway official said four bogies of the passenger
train were seriously damaged. Railway traffic on the Ambala-
Ludhiana-Amritsar and Jammu Tawa mainline sections was disrupted
due to the derailment.
</P>
<P>
The exact cause of the mishap was not known, the spokesman said,
adding that the express train, which was in the process of picking
up speed after it left Ambala Cantt, rammed from behind into the
empty rake of the passenger train, which had suddenly come to a
halt.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, an investigation has
been ordered into the accident.
</P>
<P>
Railway sources said a power failure could be one of the causes
of the sudden stoppage of the passenger train. 
