<HEADLINE> Solomon Prime Minister Pledges to Find Peaceful Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Mannesseh Sogavare, the new prime
minister of Solomon Islands, expressed his willingness to find a
peaceful resolution to the ethnic war on Guadalcanal by Christmas.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Radio Corporation reported Saturday that the
prime minister, who was elected on June 28, hoped the problem
would be settled through discussions, interactions and
negotiations. "If all goes well then I hope we should be able to
achieve lasting peace by Christmas 2000."
</P>
