<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Scientist Identifies Osteopetrosis Gene </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Renato Dulbecco, a scientist with the
Italian Institute for Advanced Biomedical Technologies, announced
Saturday the identification of the gene responsible for malignant
osteopetrosis, a fatal hereditary disease which strikes one in 100,
000 newborns.
</P>
<P>
Dulbecco, winner of the 1975 Nobel Prize for medicine,
explained in Italy's northern city Milan that the gene is
manifested as an alteration of bone structure which leads quickly
to death.
</P>
<P>
Italian news agency Ansa reported that the discovery of the
osteopetrosis gene is an important step in regulating bone
metabolism.
</P>
<P>
Dulbecco said that the results of research could lead to a
better understanding of the pathogenesis of osteoporosis, an
extremely widespread disease.
</P>
<P>
Researchers at the institute said in the case of osteopetrosis,
the bone is harder than normal and is not modeled as it should be.
</P>
<P>
The result is that the marrow is unable to produce blood cells
in the quantities needed and the cranial nerves are progressively
compressed causing blindness and ultimately death.
</P>
<P>
Dulbecco said the identification of the gene will make early
diagnosis possible, with a uterine intervention, and
identification of the carrier of the recessive gene.
</P>
<P>
All the findings will be reported in the July edition of the
journal Nature Genetics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000701.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S.: Israeli-Palestinian Talks Should Be Based on U.N. Resolutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. government on Friday
said that Israeli and Palestinian negotiations should be based on
U.N. Security Council resolutions calling on Israel to return
territory it seized in the 1967 Middle East war in exchange for
peace.
</P>
<P>
"It's our view that all negotiations should be based on
Resolutions 242 and 338, all negotiations between Israel and the
Arabs, including the negotiations between the Israelis and the
Palestinians," State Department spokesman Richard Boucher told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
"That's the framework that we've always worked in and it's the
one we believe we should continue to work in," he added.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement in response to a question about an
Israeli court decision Friday on the applicability of U.N.
Resolution 242 adopted in 1967.
</P>
<P>
Resolution 338 was adopted in 1973.
</P>
<P>
Israel's Attorney General Eliyakim Rubinstein reportedly ruled
that the Palestinian Authority could not lay claim to the West
Bank, Gaza and east Jerusalem under the resolutions because
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat's government did not exist at the
time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
