<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, July 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Director General of the United Nations Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO) Jacques Diouf arrived here Friday
on a fact-finding visit.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to focus on the tragic accident that two
staffers of the FAO office in Baghdad were killed by a gunman
Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The gunman, identified as 38-year-old Fuad Haidar, shot and
killed two FAO staffers -- a Somali and an Iraqi -- and wounded
several others.
</P>
<P>
Haidar, who surrendered to the authorities after a two-hour
confrontation with Iraqi security forces, claimed that his attack
was meant to protest the decade-old U.N. sanctions.  (Iraq-FAO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The cooperative movement can help ensure that
the benefits of globalization are shared by all, Secretary-General
Kofi Annan said on Friday, the eve of the International Day of
Cooperatives marked each year on the first Saturday in July.
</P>
<P>
"Founded on the principles of private initiative,
entrepreneurship and self-employment, underpinned by the values of
democracy, equality and solidarity, the movement can help pave the
way to a more just and inclusive economic order," the Secretary-
General said in his message on the Day.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A U.S. court committee Friday sued President Bill
Clinton in a bid to disbar him as a lawyer for denying his sexual
contact with former White House intern Monica Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
The Committee on Professional Conduct of the Arkansas Supreme
Court filed suit in Pulaski County Circuit Court, charging that
Clinton's conduct "damages the legal profession and demonstrates a
lack of overall fitness to hold a license to practice law."  (US-
Court-Clinton)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France Friday called on newly industrializing
countries and developing countries to provide help in the fight
against tax havens.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting of 29 member countries of the Organization for
Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) with 30 non-member
countries, French Finance Minister Laurent Fabius said that France
will do its best to see financial sanctions imposed on those
countries which refuse to cooperate in the fight against money
laundering.
</P>
<P>
France will present some proposals on the issue at the summit
of the Group of Eight countries in Okinawa in July. (France-Tax
Havens)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French President Jacques Chirac met with visiting
Armenian President Robert Kocharian on Friday and discussed with
the latter bilateral relations and the situation in Upper Karabakh.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said after the meeting that the relations between France
and Armenia are very important and close because of the big
Armenian community in France.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his sympathy with Armenian nation's tragic
exodus in 1915, during which hundreds of thousands of Armenians
died. (France-Armenia-Visit) 
</P>
