<HEADLINE> Bidding Set to Open for Barmby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
Everton are waiting for Liverpool to start the bidding for England
forward Nick Barmby.
</P>
<P>
The Goodison club are expecting an official approach from
Liverpool after Barmby told the Blues he wants to move across
Stanley Park to Anfield.
</P>
<P>
It is now down to Liverpool to follow up their initial interest
in Barmby after they had asked their Merseyside rivals to keep
them informed of developments.
</P>
<P>
The fee could prove to be a sticking point with the two clubs
likely to be miles apart in their valuations of the player.
</P>
<P>
Everton will at least want to recoup the 5.75 million pounds
they paid Middlesbrough for Barmby in October 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Reds may be reluctant to pay that much for a player with
just 12 months left on his contract who could join them for
nothing next summer.
</P>
<P>
Everton may consider a player in part exchange, with Titi
Camara or David Thompson being touted as possible makeweights in
any deal.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea have also been linked with Barmby and Smith has
transfer-listed him in a bid to speed up his sale regardless of
the buyer. 
