<HEADLINE> Agassi Advances, Enqvist Moves Through </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Andre Agassi of the
United States just had a narrow escape at the Wimbledon tennis
championships on Friday after saving two match points in a 6-4, 2-
6,7-6, 2-6, 10-8 victory over compatriot Todd Martin.
</P>
<P>
Ninth seed Thomas Enqvist, one of only two seeds left in the
top half of the draw, also came through a grueling five-setter
with German qualifier Christian Vinck to move into the last 16.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Pete Sampras has another day to recover from
a leg injury picked up on Wednesday after his third round match
against fellow American Justin Gimelstob was held over until
Saturday because of rain.
</P>
<P>
Women's top seed Martina Hingis swept past Croatia's Silvija
Talaja while eighth seed Serena Williams wasted little time
disposing of Cristina Torrens-Valero of Spain 6-2, 6-1 - the U.S.
Open champion has lost just nine games in three rounds.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's Byron Black sailed into the last 16 at Wimbledon for
the first time in his life and has his sights set on making the
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The unseeded Black, a rare grasscourt specialist in his half of
the draw, thrashed Spaniard Albert Portas 6-2, 6-0, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
With the early culling of seeds -- Magnus Norman, Greg Rusedski,
Richard Krajicek and Cedric Pioline have all vanished from Black's
quarter of the draw -- the veteran Zimbabwean now has no seeded
players between him and the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
He will next face Italian veteran Gianluca Pozzi, at 35 the
oldest player in the men's singles, who ended the giant-killing
run of Belgian qualifier Olivier Rochus 6-3, 3-6, 7-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Belarus qualifier Vladimir Voltchkov, a former boy's singles
champion here, defeated Younes El Aynaoui of Morocco 7-6 (7-4), 7-
5,7-6 and will play Wayne Ferreira in the last 16 after the South
African beat Andrei Pavel 3-6, 7-6, 7-5, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman steered a course into the fourth round
with a 6-3, 6-4, 6-4 victory over qualifier Neville Godwin of
South Africa. His next opponent could be top seed Sampras. 
</P>
</TEXT>
