<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scientists Worldwide Reaffirm Cause of AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 5,000 scientists from
around the world have united to prepare a resounding assertion
that HIV causes AIDS, a U.S.-based global perception management/
communication consulting firm reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to Burson-Marsteller, their statement, called the
Durban Declaration, calls for an immediate end to the debate on
the fundamental causal relationship between HIV and AIDS, noting
that the insistence of a vocal minority in denying that HIV causes
AIDS "will cost countless lives."
</P>
<P>
The name of the declaration, to be published in the coming
issue of Nature, refers to Durban, South Africa, site of the 13th
International AIDS Conference to begin July 9.
</P>
<P>
It affirms that the scientific evidence supporting the link
between HIV and AIDS is "clear-cut, exhaustive and unambiguous."
It stresses that the data, compiled from years of HIV/AIDS
research, "fulfill exactly the same criteria as for other viral
diseases, such as polio, measles and smallpox."
</P>
<P>
Among the signatories of the declaration are 11 Nobel Laureates
as well as directors of leading research institutes, academies and
medical societies.
</P>
<P>
Burson-Marsteller said that the document comes at a time when
19 million people have already died of AIDS in less than 20 years
since the emergence of the disease. More than 34 million people
are now living with HIV-AIDS, of whom 24 million live in sub-
Saharan Africa.
</P>
<P>
Among those who have challenged the virus-AIDS is Peter
Duesberg, a professor of molecular and cell biology at the
University of California-Berkeley. He has proposed the hypothesis
that the various AIDS diseases are brought on by the long-term
consumption of recreational drugs or AZT itself, which is
prescribed to prevent or treat AIDS. His Web site contains his
written works on the subject as well as other scientists,
including two Nobel prize winners, who support his views. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000701.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
