<HEADLINE> Chile To Create Fund for Exports Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean government announced
Saturday that it will have ready in one hundred days the project
for a Fund for Exports Protection, said Economy, Mining, and
Energy Minister Jose de Gregorio.
</P>
<P>
The project is the answer to businessmen concerns over the
recent abundance of accusations and threats to Chilean exports,
said De Gregorio, adding that it will be necessary to define who
will administer it.
</P>
