<HEADLINE> Mexican President Highlights Free Trade with EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mexico has today a new place in the world, said Zedillo. Free
trade is good for all the countries that take part in it, because
it promotes the growth of the economies, creates jobs, and
improves the families income.
</P>
<P>
Mexico became the second biggest trading partner with the
European Union (EU) in Latin America since it began to implement a
free trade agreement with EU last month
</P>
<P>
Mexico was the 24th biggest EU trading partner in 1998, when
the European exports to Mexico amounted to 9.3 billion U.S.
dollars and imports 4 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brazil ranked the 12th biggest trading partner with the
European bloc in 1998, importing 15.5 billion dollars worth of
products to Europe and exporting 13.2 billion dollars. 
</P>
